# Component Conventions

## Adding components

- Add new shadcn components with the CLI, never hand-create them:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <name>
```

  This keeps dependencies, structure, and theming consistent.
- Keep all UI primitives in `src/components/ui/`.

## Writing components

- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional/merged class names.
- Define variants with `cva` (class-variance-authority), mirroring the existing
  `button.tsx` pattern with `variant` + `size`:

```tsx
const buttonVariants = cva("base classes", {
  variants: { variant: { default: "...", outline: "..." } },
  defaultVariants: { variant: "default" },
})
```

- Style with theme tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`).
  Never hardcode hex or oklch colors in a component - add a token in `src/index.css` instead.

## After changing a component

- Create or update its colocated `*.stories.tsx` so the change is visible in Storybook.
